import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='cx', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude coordinates in London?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='name', y='cx', data=data)
    plt.title('Which location has the highest longitude coordinate in London?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    max_longitude = data['cx'].max()
    max_longitude_location = data.loc[data['cx'] == max_longitude, 'name'].iloc[0]
    plt.axhline(max_longitude, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Longitude: {max_longitude:.2f} ({max_longitude_location})')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
